HEADWORD: Rhodizonic
<hw>Rho`di*zon"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/<?/<?/
to be rose-red.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
designating, a colorless crystalline substance (called <xex>rhodizonic
acid</xex>, and <xex>carboxylic acid</xex>) obtained from potassium
carboxide and from certain quinones. It forms brilliant red, yellow, and
purple salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhodochrosite</ent>⟦br⟧
